{
  "texts": [
    "It follows that (M, g) is a quotient of the solvable Lie group R ⋉ D N endowed with the solvsoliton metric ds 2 + h s [Lau11] (cf.",
    "Example 2.4).",
    "The equations over a Riemann surfaceIn this section, we consider the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations (4) for a pair (B 2, G/K), where B 2 is a compact orientable surface, and G/K is an arbitrary symmetric space of non-positive curvature.",
    "If c = {e 2u ǧ: u ∈ C ∞ (B)} is a conformal class of metrics on B 2, then the pair Σ = (B 2, c) is a Riemann surface.Let (B 2, ǧ), (N, g N) be Riemannian manifolds and h: (B 2, ǧ) → (N, g N) a smooth map.",
    "Since the source is a surface, if h is harmonic with respect to ǧ, then h is also harmonic with respect to any metric conformal to ǧ."
